name: Nevada State Treasurer's Office
tweet: @PATreasury comes to #CDAForum2018 to talk about the Keystone Scholars program, claiming it will be the largest CDA program in the country.  Larger than Nevada's Kick Start? Time will tell... Can't access money without opening a PA 529. #nvleg #CollegeSavings

name: Nevada State Treasurer's Office
tweet: Due to the Tax Cuts and Jobs Act of 2017 now more than ever the design of CDA is a critical consideration. Don't worry #nvleg Kick Start is protected! #collegesavings #CDAForum2018

name: Nevada State Treasurer's Office
tweet: Thank You @csdwustl & @MOTreasurer for hosting today's amazing discussion! We appreciate your hospitality. Your investment in future generations is so important. #CDAForum2018 #CollegeSavings #NVleg

name: Nevada State Treasurer's Office
tweet: The NYC Kids Rise program focuses not just on #collegesavings, but also the financial health of the families involved in general.  Also provides account options for those nervous of investments. #CDAForum2018 #NVleg

name: Nevada State Treasurer's Office
tweet: Our office brought to #nvleg incentives to increase #CollegeSavings through the Kick Start Program. While not approved in Nevada, New York City has a program that took the idea & moved it forward. Can't wait to see the results. #cdaforum2018

name: Nevada State Treasurer's Office
tweet: Nevada's College Kick Start Program opens a $50 scholarship account for every public school Kindergartner. Academics suggest the initial funding size should be between $500 - $1000. #CDAForum #nvleg #CollegeSavings

name: Nevada State Treasurer's Office
tweet: Our office is joining seventeen states and the District of Columbia today in St. Louis at @BrownSchool to speak about Child Development Accounts. Like Nevada's College Kick Start Program. #nvleg #CDAForum #CollegeSavings
